OL,3,CWales tourism tax plans outlined as
OL,4,Cvisitors may be charged #1.25 a day
OL,6,FThe Welsh Government will publish
OL,7,Fproposals on Monday for what it calls
OL,8,Fa "visitor levy" but which opponents
OL,9,Fdescribe as a "tourism tax".
OL,11,FIt will introduce a bill into the
OL,12,FSenedd which, if it becomes law, would
OL,13,Fgive local councils the power to
OL,14,Fcharge #1.25 per person per overnight
OL,15,Fstay, including children.
OL,17,FThose staying in hostels and camping
OL,18,Fwould be charged 75p per person per
OL,19,Fovernight stay. Day visitors would not
OL,20,Fbe charged.
