OL,3,CWales tourism tax plans outlined as
OL,4,Cvisitors may be charged #1.25 a day
OL,6,F"Each council will decide how to apply
OL,7,Fthe levy based on what's best for
OL,8,Ftheir area, recognising that it may be
OL,9,Fsuitable in some parts of Wales but
OL,10,Fnot in others. Councils will carefully
OL,11,Fconsider local circumstances and
OL,12,Fensure residents are consulted before
OL,13,Fany decisions are made.
OL,15,F"We're glad to have worked closely
OL,16,Fwith the Welsh Government on this and
OL,17,Flook forward to seeing the draft
OL,18,Flegislation in the coming weeks, which
OL,19,Fwill mark an important step forward
OL,20,Ffor Wales' tourism and local
OL,21,Feconomies."
